# Accessing Survival Data

## Quick intro to survival analysis
Survival analysis is very important in biomedical research because it allows us to quantify whether a treatment or condition is associated with better or worse outcomes. In cancer research, it is commonly done to see whether a drug treatment in better patient survival compared to a control. It can also be done to see whether patients with a certain gene signature or condition exhibit better survival and outcome.

